<paragraph blockId="89.[113,1089,602,1265]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,241,602,625]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Discussion.</emphasis>
Taxonomy of the subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1913" box="[531,651,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Piazomiina">Piazomiina</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1863" box="[688,814,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Tanymecini">Tanymecini</taxonomicName>
is presently being deeply revised, in particular for Palaearctic species, and a number of new genera, new species, and revised combinations have been recently published (e.g. CHAO 1980; 
<bibRefCitation author="CHAO Y. - Ch. &amp; CHEN Y. - Q." box="[868,1085,666,689]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" pagination="85 - 107" refId="ref73830" refString="CHAO Y. - Ch. &amp; CHEN Y. - Q. 1980: (Chinese Leptomias Faust and its allied genera in the Qinhai-Xizang plateau district (Coleoptera: Curculionidae )). Entomotaxonomia 2: 85 - 107 + 2 pls. (in Chinese, English summary)." type="journal article" year="1980">CHAO &amp; CHEN 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="CHAO Y. - Ch. &amp; CHEN Y. - Q." box="[113,169,698,721]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" pagination="523 - 551" refId="ref73882" refString="CHAO Y. - Ch. &amp; CHEN Y. - Q. 1981: [Coleoptera: Curculionidae - Leptomias Faust]. Pp. 523 - 551, 3 pls. In: Insects of Xizang. Volume 1. Sciences Press, Peking, xi + 600 pp. (In Chinese)" type="book chapter" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="CHEN Y. - Q." box="[181,300,698,721]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" pagination="257 - 266" refId="ref73938" refString="CHEN Y. - Q. 1991: A revision of Leptomias Faust and descriptions of new genera and new species from Xizang, China (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Sinozoologia 8: 257 - 266." type="journal article" year="1991">CHEN 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="MAGNANO L. &amp; COLONNELLI E. &amp; CALDARA R." box="[312,540,698,721]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" refId="ref75822" refString="MAGNANO L., COLONNELLI E. &amp; CALDARA R. 2009: Order Coleoptera, superfamily Curculionoidea. Families Anthribidae, Brentidae, Apionidae, Nanophyidae, Curculionidae and Dryophthoridae. Pp. 216 - 266. HARTEN A. VAN (ed.) 2009: Arthropod fauna of the United Arab Emirates, Volume 2. Multiply Marketing Consultancy Services, Abu Dhabi, 786 pp." type="book" year="2009">MAGNANO et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
). All those authors stressed the importance of some tiny characters allowing precise definition of the genera close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schoenherr, 1840" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1840" box="[787,1088,730,753]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Piazomias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,898,730,753]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Piazomias</emphasis>
Schoenherr, 1840
</taxonomicName>
for a more natural placement of the several species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1913" box="[687,807,762,785]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Piazomiina">Piazomiina</taxonomicName>
hitherto described. On the contrary, no revisionary studies were made of the so far few African taxa described, for which we have only the outdated catalogue by 
<bibRefCitation author="GUNTHER K. &amp; ZUMPT F." box="[535,807,826,849]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" refId="ref74661" refString="GUNTHER K. &amp; ZUMPT F. 1933: Coleopterorum catalogus auspiciis et auxilio W. Junk editus a S. Schenkling. Pars 131. Curculionidae: Subfam. Tanymecinae. Junk, Berlin, 150 pp." type="book" year="1933">GÃœNTHER &amp; ZUMPT (1933)</bibRefCitation>
who listed Palaearctic and African species together. The quite subtle difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1840" box="[794,905,858,881]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Piazomias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,905,858,881]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Piazomias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire, 1882" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[963,1089,858,881]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Molybdotus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="FAIRMAIRE L." box="[113,286,890,913]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" refId="ref74192" refString="FAIRMAIRE L. 1882: [Descriptions]. In: FAIRMAIRE L., LANSBERGE &amp; BOURGEOIS V.: 8. Coleopteres recueillis par M. G. Revoil chez les Comalis. In: REVOIL G.: Faune et flore des pays Comalis (Afrique Oriental). Paris, iv + 104 pp + 1 pl." type="book" year="1882">Fairmaire, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, consisting of the presence in members of the latter genus of an often barely visible furrow separating the inner and outer part of metepisterna (
<bibRefCitation author="EMDEN F. I. VAN" box="[805,939,922,945]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" pagination="503 - 586" refId="ref74157" refString="EMDEN F. I. VAN. 1944: A key to the genera of Brachyderinae of the world. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 11 11: 503 - 586." type="journal article" year="1944">EMDEN 1944</bibRefCitation>
), although not always easy to appreciate, may be used for dividing the Palaearctic species actually belonging to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1840" box="[195,306,986,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Piazomias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[195,306,986,1009]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Piazomias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all the studied African ones which appear to belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[956,1082,986,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[956,1082,986,1009]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Molybdotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including the Socotran species, here moved from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1840" box="[651,762,1018,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Piazomias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[651,762,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Piazomias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[799,925,1018,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[799,925,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Molybdotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Waterhouse, 1881)" authorityName="Colonnelli" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermiculosus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Molybdotus vermiculosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="WATERHOUSE C. O." box="[268,464,1050,1073]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" pagination="469 - 478" refId="ref77975" refString="WATERHOUSE C. O. 1881: On the coleopterous insects collected by Prof. I. Bailey Balfour in the island of Socotra. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1881: 469 - 478, pl. XLIII." type="journal article" year="1881">Waterhouse, 1881</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[484,602,1050,1073]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="89.[113,1089,602,1265]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">
<bibRefCitation author="PERRIN H." box="[144,294,1082,1105]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" pagination="423 - 426" refId="ref76515" refString="PERRIN H. 2000: Une nouvelle espece de Curculionidae de l'ile de Socotra (Coleoptera). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 104 (1999): 423 - 426." type="journal article" year="2000">PERRIN (2000)</bibRefCitation>
cited the Socotran species as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire, 1882" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[625,1088,1082,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxepunctatus">
<emphasis box="[625,907,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Molybdotus laxepunctatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="FAIRMAIRE L." box="[916,1088,1082,1105]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" refId="ref74192" refString="FAIRMAIRE L. 1882: [Descriptions]. In: FAIRMAIRE L., LANSBERGE &amp; BOURGEOIS V.: 8. Coleopteres recueillis par M. G. Revoil chez les Comalis. In: REVOIL G.: Faune et flore des pays Comalis (Afrique Oriental). Paris, iv + 104 pp + 1 pl." type="book" year="1882">Fairmaire, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described from the nearby 
<collectingCountry box="[402,492,1114,1137]" name="Somalia" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, and since most probably was able to study Fairmaireâ€™s 
<typeStatus box="[113,163,1146,1169]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">type</typeStatus>
(s) preserved in the Paris Museum, it is probable that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1882" box="[727,910,1146,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxepunctatus">
<emphasis box="[727,910,1146,1169]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">M. laxepunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may prove to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colonnelli" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[268,446,1178,1201]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermiculosus">
<emphasis box="[268,446,1178,1201]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">M. vermiculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although only the study of the 
<typeStatus box="[792,848,1178,1201]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">types</typeStatus>
of both can solve this problem. It is worth noting, however, that 
<bibRefCitation author="FAIRMAIRE L." box="[571,757,1210,1233]" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" refId="ref74192" refString="FAIRMAIRE L. 1882: [Descriptions]. In: FAIRMAIRE L., LANSBERGE &amp; BOURGEOIS V.: 8. Coleopteres recueillis par M. G. Revoil chez les Comalis. In: REVOIL G.: Faune et flore des pays Comalis (Afrique Oriental). Paris, iv + 104 pp + 1 pl." type="book" year="1882">FAIRMAIRE (1882)</bibRefCitation>
described the scutellum of the Somali species as invisible, whereas that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Colonnelli" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[583,759,1242,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Molybdotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermiculosus">
<emphasis box="[583,759,1242,1265]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="384">M. vermiculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is small, but clearly visible.
</paragraph>
